author: LightBurn

text: While you could enjoy the story, it was more than just that. The community back then was the magic of Maplestory. Making friends, doing party quests, the free market, Orbis ship ride, etc. etc. Now it's just damage output and getting to the highest level as quick as possible. The new stuff was great though, not saying it was bad, but somewhere along those lines, what made the community great was lost.
author: Cen Ric

text: Definitely agree with Misha Xiong... it's honestly one of those games where i feel like if you didn't grow up with it when it was new and seeing someone even level 60 was a "Holy shit that dude is high level, he must be so op" moment then you won't really understand why the game is so popular... A lot has been changed and taken away from the original game and it's kind of lost it's spark to imo. Like Misha said, it's all about damage output and cubing items etc
author: MysticFate

text: You didn't miss out too much but, a lot of the maple magic it once had is not there anymore. In any case the game was only "high-quality" in the first ~40 levels of the gameplay continuum. After that it becomes a bad grind, and back in the day, it was a grind starting from level 10, even if the atmosphere was super good.
